1 forty-eight (48) hours and is not dispensed by the emergency department
2 of a hospital; or
3 3. A drug administered or dispensed to a research subject enrolled in a
4 research protocol approved by an institutional review board that has an
5 active federalwide assurance number from the United States Department
6 of Health and Human Services, Office for Human Research Protections,
7 where the research involves single, double, or triple blind drug
8 administration or is additionally covered by a certificate of
9 confidentiality from the National Institutes of Health;
10 (c) In addition to the data required by paragraph (d) of this subsection, a
11 Kentucky-licensed acute care hospital or critical access hospital shall report to
